            <h2>Ministry Opportunity at Cathcart UF</h2>

            <!-- OVERVIEW -->
            <div class="section-card">
                <div class="section-card-header">
                    <h3>We Are Seeking a Minister</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="section-card-body">
                    <p>We are seeking a minister to serve on a full-time or part-time basis who will help us
                    in our aims of &ldquo;Growing together in Christ, serving the community, sharing Jesus&rsquo;
                    love&rdquo; through worship and preaching, pastoral care and working with us in the local
                    community.</p>
                    <p>For more information please see our
                    <a href="/profile">profile document</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- CONTACT -->
            <div class="section-card">
                <div class="section-card-header">
                    <h3>Get in Touch</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="section-card-body">
                    <p>If you would like more information or to have a confidential conversation, please contact
                    our Interim Moderator:</p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Rev John Fulton</strong><br />
                        <a href="mailto:InterimModerator@cathcartuf.org.uk">InterimModerator@cathcartuf.org.uk</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- UF CHURCH PROCESS -->
            <div class="section-card">
                <div class="section-card-header">
                    <h3>Application Process</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="section-card-body">
                    <p>Anyone seeking a ministry appointment within the United Free Church of Scotland needs to
                    have completed the appropriate application process. Information on this can be obtained from
                    the United Free Church Office:</p>
                    <p>
                        <a href="mailto:office@ufcos.org.uk">office@ufcos.org.uk</a>
                    </p>
                    <p>Further information about the denomination is available at
                    <a href="https://www.ufcos.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ufcos.org.uk</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- ABOUT THE CONGREGATION -->
            <div class="section-card">
                <div class="section-card-header">
                    <h3>About Cathcart United Free Church</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="section-card-body">
                    <p>We are a small, warm and welcoming congregation in the south side of Glasgow. We worship
                    together on Sundays at 11am and meet midweek on Wednesdays at 10:30am for a Time for
                    Reflection.</p>
                    <p>We work in partnership with Cathcart Church of Scotland and Cathcart Baptist Church on a
                    number of local initiatives, including Radiate Cathcart youth ministry and Renew Wellbeing.
                    <a href="/partnerships" class="section-link">Find out more about our partnerships →</a></p>
                    <p>If you would like to visit or find out more about our congregation before making contact,
                    you are very welcome to join us on a Sunday morning or
                    <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

